<br>
The second section you quoted was just to point out that its possible not all the trains that you caught were aimed at you.  <br>
<br>
The third section quoted is really my own gripe about people who constantly come to these boards to bitch and moan about something that happened to them in game and yet never petition the issue.  I hadnt noticed you saying you had petitioned at any time, so I decided to vent a bit.  I hardly consider myself the monarch of the Ay Ro Boards <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but thanks for the chuckle.  <br>
<br>
The fourth section quoted was a response to Halo, not a response to the topic but a response to a response... if that makes any sense.<br>
<br>
I really dislike seeing people intentionally train others.  Its not something I have ever done and if I believe I have been intentionally trained (such as when someone pulls a bunch of mobs to me and they wait around long enough to say hahaha) then I petition and report immediately.  Waiting for them to do it a second or third time before doing both is doing nothing but giving those people free reign to disrupt your playing.  Also, I hardly consider petitioning and reporting harassment as running to big brother GM.  There is no reason for anyone to put up with that, and since we're not on a Zek, you have little recourse but to petition. <br>
<br>
You said you petitioned eventually, I think you might have saved yourself a lot of anguish had you petitioned immediately when you had proof of being harassed/intentionally trained. <br>
<br>
Lastly, yes I realize these boards are here for people to come and gripe about bad shit that happened to them.  But for the love of christ, I get tired of seeing people complaining about the same people over and over again when they have never petitioned.  You dont get rid of those people by coming here, you get rid of them by letting the GMs know there is a problem.<br>
<br>
This post (and my first one) were not meant in a malicious way, I hope you dont take them as such.<br>
